       [1mdeadzonesize                 [22mâ”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
              Default: 0.5          â”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
                                    â”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
              Size of the deadzone. â”‚The deadzone is â”‚an area that makes the mouse act like leaviâ”‚ng the  window.  Movement
              there  won't make the â”‚OSC show up and â”‚it will hide immediately if the mouse enterâ”‚s it. The deadzone starts
              at the window border oâ”‚pposite to the Oâ”‚SC and the size controls how much of the wiâ”‚ndow it will span. Values
              between 0.0 and 1.0, wâ”‚here 0 means theâ”‚OSC will always popup with mouse movement â”‚in  the  window,  and  1
              means the OSC will onlâ”‚y show up when tâ”‚he mouse hovers it. Default pre-0.21.0 was â”‚0.
                                    â”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
       [1mminmousemove                 [22mâ”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
              Default: 0            â”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
                                    â”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
              Minimum  amount  of piâ”‚xels the mouse hâ”‚as to move between ticks to make the OSC shâ”‚ow up. Default pre-0.21.0
              was 3.                â”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
                                    â”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
       [1mshowwindowed                 [22mâ”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
              Default: yes          â”‚               â”‚                                          â”‚
